":"1330","1 Aug 1418":"1 August 1418","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","Abt 1400":"about 1400","1382":"1382","1380":"1382","1418":"1418","Warwick, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Rutland, England":"Rutland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Laynham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh and English (West Midlands): variant of Welsh   Bennion  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bennion","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>ap Einion</i>, <i>ap Eynon</i> ‘son of <i>Einion</i>’ (see   Eynon  )."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":22,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Laynham was born in 1360, in Essex, England, his father, Robert Lainham, was 31 and his mother, Mrs Robert Lainham, was 21. He married Alice Millicent Hende in 1382, in Rutland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 1 August 1418, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1360–1 Aug 1418":"1360–1. august 1418","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1360–1446":"1360–1446","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1400":"1400","1330":"1330","1 Aug 1418":"1. august 1418","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","Abt 1400":"umbes 1400","1382":"1382","1380":"1382","1418":"1418","Warwick, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Rutland, England":"Rutland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1360–1 Aug 1418":"1360–1. elokuuta 1418","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1360–1446":"1360–1446","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1400":"1400","1330":"1330","1 Aug 1418":"1. elokuuta 1418","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","Abt 1400":"noin 1400","1382":"1382","1380":"1382","1418":"1418","Warwick, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Rutland, England":"Rutland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1360–1 Aug 1418":"1360–1 août 1418","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1360–1446":"1360–1446","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1400":"1400","1330":"1330","1 Aug 1418":"1 août 1418","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","Abt 1400":"environ 1400","1382":"1382","1380":"